nd\nmetallicity gradients. Thus, the galactic-archaeology approach of calculating\nradial star-formation histories from stellar populations at $z=0$ can be\nseverely biased. These effects are strongest at $M_{\\rm\nstar}\\approx10^{7-9.6}{\\rm M_{\\odot}}$, the same regime where feedback most\nefficiently cores galaxies. Thus, detailed measurements of stellar kinematics\nin low-mass galaxies can strongly constrain feedback models and test baryonic\nsolutions to small-scale problems in $\\Lambda$CDM.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Dec 2015 21:00:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 30 Mar 2016 22:10:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-04-01"}
