ed to classical models, with a sharp decline in mass-loss\nrate immediately after the pulse. We find that the mass-loss rate after a\nthermal pulse has to decline more slowly than generally expected from models of\nthermal pulses. This may cause the star to lose significantly more mass during\na thermal pulse cycle, which affects the chemical evolution of the star and the\ninterstellar medium.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 4 Dec 2015 09:40:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-20"}
